4 A BILL
5 TO BE ENTITLED
6 AN ACT
7
8
9 Relating to Montgomery County; to provide for the
10 creation, funding, and operation of the Montgomery County
11 Legislative Delegation Office and Fund.
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
13 Section 1. (a)(1) The Montgomery County Commission
14 shall create the Montgomery County Legislative Delegation
15 Fund. The monies in the fund may be expended by the members of
16 the delegation to support the operation of the Montgomery
17 County Legislative Delegation Office.
18 (2) Upon receipt of any monies distributed to
19 Montgomery County pursuant to Section 40-25-82, Code of
20 Alabama 1975, the county commission shall deposit up to five
21 hundred thousand dollars ($500,000) per calendar year into the
22 fund. Any additional monies received shall be deposited in the
23 county general fund.
24 (b)(1) The Montgomery County Commission shall employ a
25 full-time office manager and two full-time administrative
26 assistants to assist in the daily management of the Montgomery
27 County Legislative Delegation Office.
28 (2) The commission shall be responsible for the wages
Page 1

(2) The commission shall be responsible for the wages
HB556 INTRODUCED
29 and benefits of the office employees. The wages and benefits
30 shall be set by the Montgomery County Legislative Delegation
31 in consultation with the commission.
32 (3) The office employees shall not be subject to the
33 personnel board created pursuant to Section 45-51A-32.110,
34 Code of Alabama 1975.
35 (4) The office employees shall be selected by the
36 members of the delegation and shall serve at the pleasure of
37 the delegation.
38 (5) The office employees shall report to the chair of
39 the delegation, and the duties of the office employees shall
40 be limited to the support of the members of the delegation and
41 the delegation office.
42 (c) The largest municipality in Montgomery County shall
43 provide adequate space for the office, including telephone
44 service, Internet service, electricity, water, and any other
45 necessary utility services.
46 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
47 1, 2026.
